# Console Rules (Condensed)

- Canonical source: `AGENTS.md`.
- Project identity: Console is a local AI CLI unified management platform.
- Scope now: CLI version management, provider/model management, MCP server management, skills management, Web UI management panel.
- Keep management plane (state/config/API/sync) separate from execution plane (worker adapters).
- Use explicit CLI adapters for Claude CLI, Codex CLI, Gemini CLI, and Cursor CLI.
- Config sync engine is the core integration layer — translates unified config to each CLI's native format.
- Do not hard-code one CLI implementation into core business logic.
- Prefer simple, local-first solutions; avoid premature distributed orchestration.
- Storage default: file-based config/state under `~/.console/`; defer SQLite until justified.
- Default stack: backend Rust (axum), frontend Vite + React + Tailwind.
- Default streaming transport: SSE unless a strong reason exists.
- Keep modules small and composable; favor clarity over abstraction-heavy frameworks.
- Update docs in `docs/` when behavior or architecture changes.
- Document architectural decisions when introduced.
